<div class="wrapper has-background-white featured-articles">
<div class="container columns is-multiline is-variable is-6-desktop is-8-widescreen">
<div class="column is-full">
<h2 class="title has-text-navy-black py-5">Why Linkerd?</h2>
</div>
<div class="column is-one-third">
<a href="/2021/11/29/linkerd-vs-istio-benchmarks-2021/index.html" class="card-link">
<div class="card">
<header class="card-header px-2 py-1">
<p class="card-header-title has-text-navy-black">
Smaller and faster than any other mesh
</p>
</header>
<figure class="image">
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZwogIHdpZHRoPSI2NjAiCiAgaGVpZ2h0PSIyNDAiCiAgZmlsbD0ibm9uZSIKICB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPgo8L3N2Zz4=" data-src="/uploads/featured-articles/article-1.png" class="lazyload " alt="Smaller and faster than any other mesh" />
</figure>
<div class="card-content">
<div class="content">
Benchmarks show that Linkerd continues to be dramatically faster than Istio while consuming just a fraction of the system resources.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</a>
</div>
<div class="column is-one-third">
<a href="/design-principles/" class="card-link">
<div class="card">
<header class="card-header px-2 py-1">
<p class="card-header-title has-text-navy-black">
Designed for simplicity and security
</p>
</header>
<figure class="image">
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZwogIHdpZHRoPSI2NjAiCiAgaGVpZ2h0PSIyNDAiCiAgZmlsbD0ibm9uZSIKICB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPgo8L3N2Zz4=" data-src="/uploads/featured-articles/article-2.png" class="lazyload " alt="Designed for simplicity and security" />
</figure>
<div class="card-content">
<div class="content">
Linkerd&#39;s unique design provides fundamental visibility, reliability, and security capabilities without the complexity of other approaches.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</a>
</div>
<div class="column is-one-third">
<a href="/2020/12/03/why-linkerd-doesnt-use-envoy/" class="card-link">
<div class="card">
<header class="card-header px-2 py-1">
<p class="card-header-title has-text-navy-black">
Built in Rust, the language of the future
</p>
</header>
<figure class="image">
<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZwogIHdpZHRoPSI2NjAiCiAgaGVpZ2h0PSIyNDAiCiAgZmlsbD0ibm9uZSIKICB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPgo8L3N2Zz4=" data-src="/uploads/featured-articles/article-3.png" class="lazyload " alt="Built in Rust, the language of the future" />
</figure>
<div class="card-content">
<div class="content">
Linkerd is the only service mesh written in Rust, allowing us to confidently write secure code without the CVEs and buffer overflow exploits endemic to other languages.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
